#PoleToPole with Will Smith premieres January 13 at 9/8c on @natgeotv. Streaming on @DisneyPlus and @hulu.

Each winter in Switzerlandâ€™s Valais region, skiers take to the slopes dressed as witches for the Belalp Hexeâ€”an annual race inspired by a local legend about a sorceress and her hapless husband. What began as a playful nod to regional folklore to fill the January low season has grown into a beloved event that blends skiing, costumes, and social traditions.

Discover how this race became a modern alpine tradition at the link in bio.

Photo by @joelsartore | Seen here as a two-month-old cub is the jaguar named Teiku that calls @zoodomrd home. Jaguars are most similar in appearance to leopards, but thereâ€™s nothing you can confuse them with in South America. The most distinctive feature of jaguars is the shape of their spots, which resemble a certain sweet-smelling flower: the rose. To see more species featured in the #PhotoArk, follow me, @joelsartore.
